    "body": "This pull request includes several documentation and API improvements related to the `InjectFenceProxy` TIR pass, as well as a minor code change in an example and the addition of a new TVM intrinsic wrapper. The most significant changes are updates to the documentation for clarity and completeness, the exposure of the `allocate` function, and the addition of the `ptx_fence_barrier_init` intrinsic.\r\n\r\n**Documentation improvements for `InjectFenceProxy`:**\r\n\r\n* Expanded and clarified the `inject_fence_proxy.md` documentation to better explain the distinction between generic and async proxy operations, detail how the pass tracks proxy state, describe new coverage for shared-memory `BufferStore`, and explain how to override proxy classification with `tl.proxy_hint` annotations. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-57f29585572b0a0590f71bc955a9d64e66fc29efa2f3021d3ad8183153ac41a1L3-R31) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-57f29585572b0a0590f71bc955a9d64e66fc29efa2f3021d3ad8183153ac41a1L113-R126)\r\n\r\n**API and usability enhancements:**\r\n\r\n* Exposed the `allocate` function from `tvm.script.parser.tir` in the `tilelang.language` API for easier user access.\r\n\r\n**Intrinsic additions:**\r\n\r\n* Added a Python wrapper for the new `ptx_fence_barrier_init` TVM intrinsic in both `tilelang/language/tir/op.py` and registered it in `tilelang/language/tir/ir.py`. [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-bd28c67c32c4cb5dad2153f8c3873fd398f7d5e8332b347e35b4ce535f59d86bR1752-R1764) [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-e14f4873ec15122b0b08846a0a21eba97345bcc9befddd8fc77482b84f7a697cR264)\r\n\r\n**Example code update:**\r\n\r\n* Uncommented the code in `examples/quickstart.py` to print the generated CUDA kernel source, making it easier for users to inspect the output.\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Quickstart now prints the generated CUDA kernel source\n  * New public symbol exposed: allocate\n  * Added ptx_fence_barrier_init intrinsic\n\n* **Documentation**\n  * Expanded fence-proxy guide with clearer transition semantics, examples, SM90 coverage, and guidance for custom/opaque ops\n\n* **Tests**\n  * Large test suite validating fence-proxy injection, async intrinsics, ordering, normalization, and deduplication\n\n* **Bug Fixes / Reliability**\n  * Ensured synchronization ordering for async/bulk stores and atomic-reduction paths to prevent reuse/race issues\n\n* **Refactor**\n  * Fence-proxy pass rewritten to a stateful, control-flow-aware model with conservative merges and hint handling\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
